The Refinerys MOC process is required for changes to procedures, work instructions, and manuals other than minor clarifications related to formatting, grammar, and typos. Any revised documents are routed through the Refinery Business Unit (RBU) for review and approval.
In addition, at the end of each calendar year, each RBU Manager is required to certify that the operating procedures for their area are current and accurate as part of the Richmond Refinerys annual compliance certification process.

