All required approvals must be obtained and any PSSR Items documented prior to startup. PSSR Items are incomplete tasks or discrepancies that will need to be resolved. The PSSR facilitator and the appropriate RBU Manager (or delegate) must review and agree on PSSR Items prior to startup of the system/unit or equipment. PSSR Items will be tracked to completion. Each PSSR Item will be specific, assigned to an individual, have a due date and be identified as required or not required prior to startup. 

PSSR records are maintained for a minimum of 5 years.

i. Compliance Audits  
Knowledgeable Chevron personnel perform internal compliance audits at least every three years. Audits help certify compliance with regulations and ensure that process safety systems function in a manner to protect the community, the environment and employees from accidental releases of highly hazardous chemicals.

