k. Employee Participation 
The Refinery relies on the expertise of Chevron employees and contractors at all levels and disciplines to optimize safe and reliable operations. This is achieved by consulting with Refinery workers to ensure consideration of their knowledge and experience in all applicable areas of the prevention program. The Refinerys Employee Participation Plan fosters ongoing engagement between management, employees and contractors. It encourages active participation in the design, development, implementation and continual improvement of process safety activities and systems. Worker involvement will help ensure that all perspectives are considered and that the best ideas are implemented.

The Employee Participation Plan ensures that:
- Refinery workers are consulted on, and can participate in, PHAs, DMRs, LOPAs, Incident Investigations, HCAs, and MOCs. Other employees with responsibilities relating to specific processes are consulted prior to and during the elements listed above. Worker involvement is documented in reports.  
- All Refinery employees are given an opportunity to provide feedback on Refinery Instruction updates. 
- Operations and Maintenance workers and their representatives are consulted on the development of all prevention program elements and the Emergency Response Program. Examples of participation include the following:
(a) Development and review of procedures, with participation documented in the EMMS;
(b) Development and revision of Refinery Instructions;
(c) Integral members of Incident Investigation teams, with participation documented in the incident report;
